description: As the election draws near, Cuba becomes a powder keg. The exactions of El Santero continue, terrifying the liberators-turned-occupiers and enflaming the spirit of the freedom-starved Cubans. In response, American authorities don’t hesitate to use extreme violence to ensure that their candidate will win and become not the president of the Republic of Cuba, but the first governor of the 46th state. For the SPOOKS, torn between duty and convictions, the danger is real, and choices will have to be made…
name: The 46th State

Shi ga Futari wo Wakatsu made

description: Wayne Shelton is ready to proceed with the mission and spring his quarry from a Khalak prison. There is a small concern over Madrier, the Frenchman who talked his way onto the team – only to abandon them after he was revealed to be the son of a Khalak dissident… A job’s a job, though, and Shelton gave his word to his employer. But what if there are other separate, secret interests among the little band that could jeopardize everything?
name: The Betrayal

description: The Cold War: the golden age of American and Soviet spies, a time when everything was clear-cut and simple. We’re the good guys, they’re the bad guys. Nowadays, CIA operatives like Alpha often feel more like commercial envoys than secret agents. When bodies start to drop in Washington, though, a boring mission playing tourist guide to a Russian delegation suddenly becomes much more dangerous. An old bogeyman from the Cold War, long thought dead, has reappeared…
name: Sanctions
You've Got a Friend, Charlie Brown

name: Wash Tubbs

description: Brains' BMX is broken, just when there's a big race coming up with the main prize being the ultimate racing bike! Brains is desperate and wants to use a muscle enhancing drink to win the game. But he hasn't counted on his greatest rival! Steven Stunt also wants to win the race and plays the cheating game: oil spills, nails on the road, everything goes. Who will come out on top?
name: Zwijgen En Trappen

description: Besides skateboarding, Dweezil wants to try something else: he buys a cheap snowboard! Small problem: he's forgotten it's the middle of summer. Not a speck of snow for miles around. It seems Dweezil has to be patient, but then Brains has a brilliant plan! He will make Dweezil snowboard within a day!
name: Freeze!

description: Armando finds an egg-shaped object that came from outer space. When Brains examins the object, an alien suddenly crawls out of it. Ferre the iron-eater. It wants to solve the famine on its own planet by getting iron at other solar systems. The friends of Jump are spied on, however, by a gangster who wants to use Ferre for his own criminal plans.
name: De IJzervreter!

description: Brains has a new addiction: a supercool, incredible computer game. Lisa and Dweezil are not happy with their friend spending all his time playing the game. They decide to teach him a lesson. That plan goes horribly wrong, because now they're in the game itself!
name: Game Over!

description: Dweezil lets himself be persuaded to take part in a very strange contest: he must deliver the head of a statue to an island in the Atlantic Ocean within 48 hours. On the island is the rest of the statue. If he succeeds, a fantastic prize awaits him: a date with... Fanny Kiekeboe, Dweezil's dream woman! And on top of that, the statue is of Marcel Kiekeboe. This story has everything to keep you at the edge of your skateboard!
name: De Kop Van Kiekeboe

volume.name: Hero: The Extraordinary Story of an Ordinary Guy

description:
Featuring thirteen complete fantasy stories, from sword-and-sorcery to slice-of-life, Fablewood features the creations of Ryan Ottley and Manny Trembley, Flight alumni JP Ahonen and Sarah Mensinga, and Chris Studabaker with his Day Prize-nominated tale which Dave Sim called 'evocative, austere and expressionistic'.

Stories

  1. Solace
  2. Die a Hero
  3. A Vicious Circle
  4. The Spirits & the Woods
  5. Mandala
  6. Blessings
  7. J'nee, Where Are You?
  8. The Ancient Pact
  9. Under the Midnight Sun
  10. Unworthy
  11. Fish
  12. A Tale of Two Shifters
  13. The Cloudleapers of Blue Pine Mountain
name: Anthology

deck: One of the short-lived Charlton 25¢ "Big Book" comics.
description: Charlton briefly tried putting out 25-cent giant-sized books such as this one. Sales flopped, and they went quickly back to the ten-cent standard.

A very old millionaire wants to be young again and asks his scientist son to invent something that gives him back his youth. Dweezil comes in touch with the invention and becomes a toddler, with all sorts of consequences! Will Brains succeed to restore Dweezil to his right age? And what are the plans of the greedy daughter-in-law of the millionaire?
name: De Kleuterdynamo

description: For centuries there's an old, decayed house in Brains', Lisa's and Dweezil's village. And for decades, a strange old lady lives there. So when Lisa suddenly sees a young girl enter the house, that's big news. Rebekka is however not a sympathetic young lady, she looks down on Lisa and her friens and acts very arrogant. When she suddenly acts very nice, there must be something behind it...
name: Het Geheim Van Vrankensteen

description:
When Dweezil ends up in a mysterious tattoo parlor, he receives an ancient bottle of black ink from the owner, an old chinese man. The ink apparently has special powers!

Meanwhile, Lisa and Brains clean up the Jump-clubhouse, that looks like a battlefield after the explosion of issue 6. During their cleanup, they discover a giant egg that seems to have come from an ostrich. When Brains examines the egg, he makes a great discovery!
name: De Tijd-Tattoo

description: Thanks to Brains' father, the whole gang can go to an aquarium park in France for free. Brains is looking for a girlfriend for his lonely clownfish, Dweezil falls head over feet for Juliette and Lisa is not charmed by Dweezil's new crush. Then they hear that the president of France will visit the park...
name: Haai Five!

description: There's something growing between Dweezil and Juliette and she invites him for a trip to south Italy. Dweezil immediately says yes, but the trip becomes a hel: Napels is full off trash and orange pulp because the maffia holds the city in its grip. And to make matters worse, Juliette looks exactly like Roma, the missing daughter of Don Cornichone. When his maffia minions see Dweezil kiss a girl that look exactly like the daughter of their boss, they decide to kidnap him! Will Dweezil be able to escape the clutches of the maffia?
name: Pulp Fictie

description: With one choice, Sara Ehret gave up a normal life and embraced her destiny as the vigilante Jackpot. But the underworld isn't about to go down without a fight, as Jackpot finds herself locked in combat with a resurgent White Rabbit and in the crosshairs of The Rose. And not even the wisdom and friendship of Spider-Man and Mister Fantastic will be enough to help her as the all-new, all-deadly Boomerang closes in for the kill. And if she survives all that, will she be ready for the biggest challenge of her young super hero career?!

name: Une pour tous et tous pour elle
